I"t<h2 id="module-3-install-configure-and-manage-enterprise-services"><strong>Module 3: Install, configure and manage enterprise services</strong></h2>

<h1 id="hands-on-activity-6-install-configure-and-manage-enterprise-services-via-ansible"><strong>Hands-on Activity 6: Install, configure, and manage enterprise services via Ansible</strong></h1>

<h1 id="procedure"><strong>Procedure</strong></h1>
<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Fork this repository https://github.com/ajcanlas-tip/sysad2-12021.git</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Clone your newly forked repository.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Make a new branch named ‚Äúactivity6‚Äù from master branch using git branch activity6 and git checkout activity6</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Make a new new remote upstream with git remote add upstream https://github.com/ajcanlas-tip/sysad2-12021.git</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Create a playbook that installs dhcpd, bind9, vsftpd, samba, httpd, mariadb in both Ubuntu and Centos (use Roles to optimize the playbook)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Create different plays in installing per service and identify it as a group in Inventory file.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>add,commit and push it to your activity6 branch</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Request a pull request for the master branch in https://github.com/ajcanlas-tip/sysad2-12021.git  and activity6 branch of your forked repository.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<h1 id="output"><strong>Output</strong></h1>

<p><a href="https://github.com/mlaabelong/sysad2-12021/tree/activity6">https://github.com/mlaabelong/sysad2-12021/tree/activity6</a></p>

