<h1 id="hands-on-midterm-exam"><strong>Hands-on Midterm Exam</strong></h1>

<h1 id="procedure-4"><strong>Procedure</strong></h1>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Fork this repository https://github.com/ajcanlas-tip/sysad2-12021.git (Links to an external site.)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Clone your new repository in your VM https://github.com/&lt; your username &gt;/sysad2-12021.git</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Create a branch named ‚Äúmidterm-exam‚Äù and checkout in that branch.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Create an Ansible playbook that does the following with an input of a config.yaml file and arranged Inventory file:</p>

    <p>4.1 Install and configure Elastic Stack in separate  hosts (Elastic Search, Kibana, Logstash)</p>

    <p>4.2 Install Nagios in one host</p>

    <p>4.3 Install Grafana,Prometheus and Influxdb in seperate hosts (Influxdb,Grafana,Prometheus)</p>

    <p>4.4 Install Lamp Stack in seperate hosts (Httpd + Php,Mariadb)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>push and commit your midterm-exam branch in the VM (no need for ansible.cfg upon pushing)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>request a pull request from that branch in GitHub</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>For your midterm exam to be counted, please paste your repository link as an answer in this exam.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<h1 id="output-5"><strong>Output</strong></h1>

<p><a href="https://github.com/mlaabelong/sysad2-12021/tree/midterm-exam">https://github.com/mlaabelong/sysad2-12021/tree/midterm-exam</a></p>

